                            <comment id="15542651" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 3 Oct 2016 15:19:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user fholger opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2581&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2581&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4709&quot; title=&quot;InputStreamFSInputWrapper does not close wrapped stream&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-4709&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-4709&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Fix resource leak in InputStreamFSInputWrapper&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    InputStreamFSInputWrapper is a wrapper around an arbitrary Java InputStream. As such, it needs to reimplement the close() function and forward it to the wrapped stream, otherwise there is a potential resource leak. This PR forwards the close() call to the underlying stream.&lt;/p&gt;

